 Yoruba activist, Sunday Adeyemo, on Monday morning claimed soldiers invaded his Ibadan residence in a bid to arrest him and his supporters. Sunday Adeyemo, a self-styled Yoruba activist, on Monday morning claimed soldiers invaded his Ibadan residence in a bid to arrest him and his supporters. Mr Adeyemo, popularly known as Sunday Igboho, raised the alarm through his spokesperson, Olayomi Koiki, who ran a live Facebook Broadcast at the car park of the activist’s residence. Mr Koiki, who kept lampooning federal and state authorities, claimed soldiers invaded Mr Igboho’s residence at around 2 am Monday morning but that they were being resisted. Gunshots could be heard intermittently in the background as Mr Koiki spoke. He claimed soldiers were doing the shooting